reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 2, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Works perfect. Will be ordering more in future.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 27, 2018
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars SO MUCH EASIER THAN FLOPPY DISKS
reviews.reviewText: I like the various colors, and each one has "16 GB" etched on the metal sleeve. Also the drives are nicely packaged in a protective box. And the labels fit just right. Another touch --- the green one, but not the black one(?) has an LED light inside that flashes when the memory is in use. I haven't tried the other 3 yet. These are now inexpensive enough to just load with photos and give away.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 13, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I’m planning to scan and save a number of documents for different types of business. This is keeping me organized.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 15, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars It has lights
reviews.reviewText: This was my first time loading a stick drive. I didn't know when I bought it but there is a light on it that blinks when it is loading or unloading files. When it's done the light doesn't blink. Very helpful. My computer is older, but this worked great with it. Would recommend it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars One out of 5 did not work
reviews.reviewText: Plugged in the memory stick downloaded 3GB of data onto the red one and it stopped working. Can no longer see it in Windows Explorer. Checked all my drivers, tried it on a different PC with same results.Only option is to send all 5 back for replacement.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 12, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Handy to carry

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 12, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Product at a Great Price
reviews.reviewText: I read some reviews that said these didn't work, but I ordered them anyway. So far, I've used two out of the five, and they worked perfectly! I will be ordering more since it seems my clients don't have CD drives anymore. I was glad to find these 1GB size since I didn't need high-capacity for basically one-time use transfer of documents. I'm not sure what to do with my massive inventory of blank CDs and CD labels:(

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 26, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Just what I needed!
reviews.reviewText: New car...no CD...no problem! (Can't stand satellite radio; want to listen to what I want to listen to when I want to listen to it! NOT an audio streamer at all. Had about 200+ CDs on HD of previous can(s)) So, my music needs to be via phone or USB and bluetooth audio quality (in my situation) is inferior to USB. Bought a 5-pack of 4g Enfain drives; have copied to and used 4 and couldn't be more pleased.1) Like the "feel" of what certainly seems to be quality construction that indicates a long life; metal "frame" surrounding plastic drive body, solid swivel and simply impressive in regard to quality of the product.2) Same as many available, I like the color "coding"3) Convenient to label! With ample supply of labels re-labeiing will be possible...without creating some kind of mess.4) Drives came very well packaged in a plastic tray in a "windowed" box. Very nice touches, indeed.5) May not be needed, but a small info/instruction pamphlet is provided! With specs, FAQs and descriptions. Little things that indicate the concern the manufacturer/seller has for the consumer. I appreciate those things!6) If one desires, engraving on the metal "frame" is available.Have ordered another set of 5...and more in the future if necessary.
Los acabados en el producto son bueno, tiene buena presentación y la capacidad es la correcta. Lo volvería a comprar.
